{{hide| 15. {{anchor|C15}} Superseded by lead rewrite |headerstyle=text-align:left; font-weight:normal; |content=
Supersedes [[#C4|#4]]. There is no consensus to change the formulation of the paragraph which summarizes election results in the lead (starting with "{{tq|Trump won the general election on November 8, 2016, …}}"). Accordingly the pre-RfC text ([[Special:Permalink/759042712|Diff 8 Jan 2017]]) has been restored, with minor adjustments to past tense ([[Special:Diff/764846021|Diff 11 Feb 2018]]). No new changes should be applied without debate. ([[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 49#RfC: Election summary in the lede|RfC Feb 2017]], [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 43#Rephrasing|Jan 2017]], [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 49#Third paragraph|Feb 2017]], [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 49#Back to process|Feb 2017]]) In particular, there is no consensus to include any wording akin to "losing the popular vote". ([[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 55#RfC: How to describe the popular vote outcome|RfC March 2017]]) (Superseded by [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 60#Options about popular vote|local consensus]] on {{diff||782425456||26 May 2017}} and [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 62#Lede Section Rewrite|lead section rewrite]] on {{diff||786987868||23 June 2017}})
}}

{{hide| 16. {{anchor|C16}} Superseded by lead rewrite |headerstyle=text-align:left; font-weight:normal; |content=
Do not mention Russian influence on the presidential election in the lead section. ([[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 51#RFC on Russian influence in election paragraph in opening|RfC March 2017]]) (Superseded by [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 62#Lede Section Rewrite|lead section rewrite]] on {{diff||786987868||23 June 2017}})
}}

{{hide| 17. {{anchor|C17}} Superseded by [[#C50|#50]] |headerstyle=text-align:left; font-weight:normal; |content=
Supersedes [[#C11|#11]]. The lead paragraph is "{{tq|'''Donald John Trump''' (born June 14, 1946) is the 45th and current [[president of the United States]]. Before entering politics, he [[Business career of Donald Trump|was a businessman]] and [[Media career of Donald Trump|television personality]].}}" The hatnote is simply {{t|Other uses}}. ([[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 56#Why is "incumbent" necessary in the hatnote?|April 2017]], [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 56#Request for comments (RFC) about whether the lead paragraph should say he's the current president|RfC April 2017]], [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 56#Which one of the proposed lede sentences will best describe Trump's current status as president?|April 2017]], [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 58#Survey about "full time" in lead paragraph|April 2017]], [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 59#'Prior to' or 'before'|April 2017]], [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 64#EGG compliance in the first sentence|July 2017]], [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 94#When to capitalize "president"?|Dec 2018]]) Amended by [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 62#Lede Section Rewrite|lead section rewrite]] on {{diff||786973475||23 June 2017}} and [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 87#Lead sentence - "in office since January 20, 2017"|removal of inauguration date]] on {{diff||848763932||4 July 2018}}. Lower-case "p" in "president" per [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 94#When to capitalize "president"?|Dec 2018]] and [[Wikipedia talk:Manual of Style/Capital letters/Archive 25#RfC 2: Specific proposal to revise the third bullet of MOS:JOBTITLES|MOS:JOBTITLES RfC Oct 2017]]. Wikilinks modified per [[Special:PermanentLink/953636518#Can we find a way to link to Presidency of Donald Trump in the first paragraph?|April 2020]]. Wikilink modified again per [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 120#Moving the link for Trump's presidency|July 2020]]. "45th" de-linked. ([[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 130#Survey: Linking of "45th" in lead|Jan 2021]])
}}

