'''22.''' {{anchor|C22}} Do not call Trump a "liar" in Wikipedia's voice. Falsehoods he uttered can be mentioned, while being mindful of calling them "lies", which implies malicious intent. ([[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 65#RFC on use of Liar and Lie|RfC Aug 2017]], upheld by [[Talk:Donald Trump/Archive 172#RfC: Should consensus 22 (not calling Trump a "liar" in Wikipedia's voice) be cancelled?|RfC July 2024]])

